\frac{dy}{dx} = 3y +1.
y = \pm C \frac{e^x}{3} - \frac{1}{3}.
3
y = Ce^x - \frac{1}{3}.
C
\frac{dy}{dx} = \frac{d}{dx}\left(Ce^x - \frac{1}{3}\right) = C\frac{d}{dx}e^x - \frac{d}{dx}\frac{1}{3} = Ce^x.
3y + 1 = 3Ce^x - 1 + 1 = 3Ce^x
\frac{d}{dx}\left( \pm \frac{Ce^x}{3} - \frac{1}{3}\right) = \pm\frac{C}{3}\frac{d}{dx}e^x = \pm\frac{C}{3}e^x,
3\left(\pm\frac{Ce^x}{3}-\frac{1}{3}\right) + 1 = \pm Ce^x\neq \pm\frac{Ce^x}{3}.
3y+1=0
y=-\frac{1}{3}
\frac{dy}{dx} = 3y+1,
K=0
\text{Either }y=-\frac{1}{3}\quad\text{or}\quad y = Ke^{3x}-\frac{1}{3}\text{ with }K\text{ non-zero.}
 y = Ke^{3x} - \frac{1}{3},\quad K\text{ an arbitrary constant.}
